   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "'# Check for duplicate characters\\n\\n```python\\ndef has_duplicates(s: str) -> bool:\\n    \"\"\"Return True if string has duplicate characters.\"\"\"\\n    return len(s) != len(set(s))\\n```\\n\\n**Usage:**\\n```python\\nprint(has_duplicates(\"hello\"))      # True (\\'l\\' appears twice)\\nprint(has_duplicates(\"world\"))      # False\\nprint(has_duplicates(\"programming\")) # True\\n```\\n\\n**Alternative (returns which chars are duplicated):**\\n```python\\ndef get_duplicates(s: str) -> set:\\n    \"\"\"Return set of duplicate characters.\"\"\"\\n    seen = set()\\n    return {c for c in s if c in seen or seen.add(c)}\\n```\\n\\nThe first approach is O(n) time and space. The second shows which characters are actually duplicated.'"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 3,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
